The paper discusses a new indicator for field normalization in citation analysis, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The use of fractional citation counting is also mentioned, which is commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and digital libraries (cs.DL). The topic of normalization is also relevant to social networks (cs.SI), cybersecurity (cs.CR), and cyberinfrastructure (cs.CY).
